{
  "texts": [
    "Function: a function is a programming structure that performs specific tasks.",
    "Microservice: a microservice is a collection of functions that can perform target system operations and is a service component.",
    "From the perspective of continuous integration and release, a microservice is an atomic entity.",
    "Any change in the internal functionality of a microservice triggers a change in that specific microservice, and new releases are triggered through the pipeline associated with that microservice without affecting the entire system.",
    "Service: service is a complete set of functions that are bundled together to achieve business goals."
  ]
}